abstract: Findings by a federal safety agency support Toyota’s claim that it had identified and was fixing the reasons that its vehicles might accelerate out of control.
snippet: Findings by a federal safety agency support Toyota’s claim that it had identified and was fixing the reasons that its vehicles might accelerate out of control.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT  The government’s investigation into complaints of sudden acceleration of Toyota vehicles has found no evidence of flawed electronics in 58 of the vehicles that crashed, federal regulators said Tuesday.

headline.main: Early U.S. Tests Find No Toyota Flaw in Electronics
headline.print_headline: U.S. Tests Find No Toyota Flaw In Electronics
